What’s under the shingles is just as important as the shingles themselves.  Our team always tears everything off down to the wood decking.  This is to ensure we can find and replace any damaged material.
.
The next step is to install membranes and flashings in any areas that could allow water to penetrate the roof system.  We then install an underpayment over the entire roof.  The underpayment is an extra layer of protection against any water that finds its way under a shingle.
.
